{{multiple issues|{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}{{update|date=July 2018}} }} A '''rapid organ recovery ambulance''' is "a special [[ambulance]] to collect the [[Cadaver|bodies]] of people who have died suddenly from [[Myocardial infarction|heart attacks]], accidents and other [[Emergency|emergencies]] and try to preserve their [[Organ (anatomy)|organs]]."<ref name=Stein>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/05/23/AR2008052303006.html |title=N.Y. Planning Special Ambulance To Recover Organs |first=Rob |last=Stein |publisher=Washington Post |date=2008-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/blogs/humannature/archive/2008/05/27/meat-wagons.aspx |title=Meat Wagons |first=William |last=Saletan |author-link=William Saletan |publisher=Slate |date=2008-03-27}}</ref> [[New York City]] is launching a [[Pilot experiment|pilot program]] deploying one such ambulance with a $1.5 million, three-year [[Grant (money)|grant]].<ref name=Stein/>
