[[File:Non-smoking.JPG|The international no smoking sign is posted in all bars and restaurants but is almost always ignored in Albania|thumb|right|250px]] '''Smoking in Albania''' is prevalent as about 40% of [[Albanians]] smoke regularly.<ref name="setimes.com">{{cite web | url= http://www.setimes.com/cocoon/setimes/xhtml/en_GB/newsbriefs/setimes/newsbriefs/2011/05/31/nb-08 | title= Albania ranks second in Europe for smoking rate | publisher= setimes.com | date= 2011-05-31 | accessdate = 3 March 2012 }}</ref> In [[Europe]], only [[Smoking in Turkey|Turkey]] has a higher smoking rate than Albania.<ref name="setimes.com" /> [[Albanians]] annually spend more than €300 million on [[tobacco]] products.<ref name="balkaninsight">{{cite web | url= http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/albania-launches-effort-to-enforce-smoking-ban | title= Albania Strengthens Crackdown on Public Smoking | last= Likmeta | first= Besar | publisher= balkaninsight.com | date= 30 Nov 2011 | accessdate =3 March 2012 }}</ref> Albania adopted tough anti-smoking laws in 2007, but they are not strictly enforced.<ref name="balkaninsight" /> Smoking prevalence is increasing, especially among females ages 13 to 15.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.tobacco.org/news/166674.html | title= Smoking: A Major Health Issue in Albania | publisher= tobacco.org | date= 2004-06-14 | accessdate = 3 March 2012 }}</ref> The smoking rate for teens between the ages of 13 and 15 is currently 15%.<ref name="balkaninsight" />
Although the law technically forbids the smoking of [[cigarette]]s in public spaces like [[Albanian cuisine|restaurants]], bars, work places, etc., Albanians regularly smoke in those places, especially nights and weekends. The smoking ban is generally followed on [[public transport]] in [[Tirana]] as people put out cigarettes before boarding buses.
[[Zog I of Albania]] was reported to smoke 200 cigarettes a day, making him possibly the heaviest smoker of his generation.<ref>{{cite web|title=King Zog|url=http://www.albanianroyalcourt.al/pages/kingzog|publisher=Albanian Royal Family|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
